    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>potatoes </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, stirring occasionally, or until golden and crisp</p><p>Once golden, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for a further 30 secs or until fragrant – these are your <strong>sauteed</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong></p>",
